<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.25%;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">5</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always" />
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Skyline Champion Corporation</span></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;" id="NOTES_TO_CONDENSED_CONSOLIDATED_FINANCIA">Notes to Condensed Consolidated Financial Statements</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000294" name="us-gaap:BusinessDescriptionAndBasisOfPresentationTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true" continuedAt="F_000294_dcnt_12ac4e75-e969-462b-913d-a3a5a4121138">
<div style="align:left;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.25%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1.</span></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Basis of Presentation and Business</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">On June 1, 2018, Skyline Champion Corporation (formerly known as Skyline Corporation), an Indiana corporation (the &#8220;Company&#8221;), and Champion Enterprises Holdings, LLC (&#8220;Champion Holdings&#8221;) completed the transactions contemplated by the Share Contribution &#38; Exchange Agreement (the &#8220;Exchange Agreement&#8221;), dated as of January 5, 2018, by and between the Company and Champion Holdings. Under the Exchange Agreement, (i) Champion Holdings contributed to the Company all of the issued and outstanding equity interests of each of Champion Holdings&#8217; wholly-owned operating subsidiaries (the &#8220;Contributed Shares&#8221;), and (ii) in exchange for the Contributed Shares, the Company issued to the members of Champion Holdings, in the aggregate, <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlishares" id="F_000326" name="us-gaap:CommonStockSharesIssued" contextRef="C_0000090896_deiLegalEntityAxis_skyChampionEnterprisesHoldingsLLCMember_20180105" decimals="INF" format="ixt:numdotdecimal">47,752,008</ix:nonFraction> shares of Company common stock (&#8220;Skyline Common Stock&#8221;) (such issuance, the &#8220;Shares Issuance&#8221;). Immediately following the Shares Issuance, the members of Champion Holdings collectively held <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000327" name="sky:OwnershipPercentage" contextRef="C_0000090896_deiLegalEntityAxis_skyChampionEnterprisesHoldingsLLCMember_20180105" decimals="3" scale="-2">84.5</ix:nonFraction>%, and the Company&#8217;s pre-closing shareholders collectively held <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000328" name="us-gaap:MinorityInterestOwnershipPercentageByNoncontrollingOwners" contextRef="C_0000090896_srtOwnershipAxis_skyIndianaCorporationMember_20180105" decimals="3" scale="-2">15.5</ix:nonFraction>%, of the issued and outstanding Skyline Common Stock on a fully-diluted basis. The contribution of the Contributed Shares by Champion Holdings to Skyline, and the Shares Issuance by the Company to the members of Champion Holdings are collectively referred to herein as the &#8220;Exchange.&#8221;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Exchange was treated as a purchase of the Company by Champion Holdings for accounting and financial reporting purposes. As a result, the financial results for the nine months ending December 29, 2018 are comprised of the results of 1) Champion Holdings for the period between April 1, 2018 and May 31, 2018 and 2) the Company, after giving effect to the Exchange, from June 1, 2018 through December 29, 2018.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The accompanying unaudited condensed consolidated financial statements of the Company, have been prepared pursuant to the rules and regulations of the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#8220;SEC&#8221;) for Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q and Article 10 of SEC Regulation S-X. Accordingly, certain information and footnote disclosures normally included in financial statements prepared in accordance with United States Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (&#8220;U.S. GAAP&#8221;) have been condensed or omitted pursuant to such rules and regulations.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The condensed consolidated financial statements include the accounts of the Company and its majority-owned subsidiaries after elimination of intercompany balances and transactions. In the opinion of management, these statements include all normal recurring adjustments necessary to fairly state the Company&#8217;s consolidated results of operations, cash flows and financial position. The Company has evaluated subsequent events after the balance sheet date through the date of the filing of this report with the SEC. These condensed consolidated financial statements should be read in conjunction with the audited consolidated financial statements and the notes to the audited consolidated financial statements included in the Company&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K, which was filed with the SEC on May 23, 2019.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The preparation of financial statements in conformity with U.S. GAAP requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the amounts reported in the condensed consolidated financial statements and the accompanying notes thereto. Actual results could differ from those estimates. The condensed consolidated statements of comprehensive income (loss) and condensed consolidated statements of cash flows for the interim periods are not necessarily indicative of the results of operations or cash flows for the full year.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company&#8217;s fiscal year is a 52- or 53-week period that ends on the Saturday nearest to March 31. The Company&#8217;s current fiscal year, &#8220;fiscal 2020&#8221;, will end on&#160;March&#160;28, 2020. References to &#8220;fiscal 2019&#8221; refer to the Company&#8217;s fiscal year ended March 30, 2019. The three and nine months ended December 28, 2019 and December 29, 2018 each included 13 weeks and 39 weeks, respectively.&#160;&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company&#8217;s operations consist of manufacturing, retail and transportation activities. The Company operates <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_skyFacility" id="F_000329" name="sky:NumberOfManufacturingFacilities" contextRef="C_0000090896_srtStatementGeographicalAxis_countryUS_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF">33</ix:nonFraction> manufacturing facilities throughout the United States (&#8220;U.S.&#8221;) and <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_skyFacility" id="F_000330" name="sky:NumberOfManufacturingFacilities" contextRef="C_0000090896_srtStatementGeographicalAxis_countryCA_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen">five</ix:nonFraction> manufacturing facilities in western Canada that primarily construct factory-built, timber-framed manufactured, and modular houses that are sold primarily to independent retailers and builders/developers. The Company&#8217;s retail operations consist of <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_skyCenter" id="F_000331" name="sky:NumberOfSalesCenters" contextRef="C_0000090896_srtStatementGeographicalAxis_countryUS_20191228" decimals="INF">21</ix:nonFraction> sales centers that sell manufactured houses to consumers primarily in the Southern U.S. The Company&#8217;s transportation business engages independent owners/drivers to transport recreational vehicles throughout the U.S. and Canada and manufactured houses in certain regions of the U.S. </p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000309" name="us-gaap:NewAccountingPronouncementsPolicyPolicyTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true" continuedAt="F_000309_dcnt_490c96fc-196e-4fa9-8e3c-ab9b1e47aea8">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Recently Adopted Accounting Pronouncements: <span style="font-style:normal;">In February&#160;2016, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#8220;FASB&#8221;) issued Accounting Standards Update (&#8220;ASU&#8221;) 2016-02, </span>Leases<span style="font-style:normal;"> </span>(Topic 842) <span style="font-style:normal;">(&#8220;ASC 842&#8221;), to increase transparency and comparability among organizations by recognizing lease assets and lease liabilities on the balance sheet and disclosing key information about leasing arrangements. A lessee should recognize in the consolidated balance sheet a liability to make lease payments (the lease liability) and an asset representing its right to use the underlying asset for the lease term. The recognition, measurement, and presentation of expenses and cash flows arising from a lease by a lessee have not significantly changed from previous requirements. This ASC 842 is effective for fiscal years beginning after December&#160;31, 2018 and modified retrospective application is permitted. </span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company adopted ASC 842 as of March 31, 2019, the first day of fiscal 2020 using the modified retrospective approach and without restating comparative periods. The Company has elected to apply the transition package of three practical expedients which allow companies not to reassess whether agreements contain leases, the classification of leases, and the capitalization of initial direct costs. The Company did not elect the practical expedient which permits the use of hindsight when determining the lease term and assessing right-of-use assets for impairment. As permitted by the standard, the Company elected to: 1) recognize lease expense for leases with a term of 12 months or less on a straight-line basis over the lease term and will not recognize any right of use assets or lease liabilities for those leases, and 2) not separate lease and non-lease components. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</p></ix:nonNumeric></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">6</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always" />
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Skyline Champion Corporation</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Notes to Condensed Consolidated Financial Statements - Continued</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p><ix:continuation id="F_000294_dcnt_12ac4e75-e969-462b-913d-a3a5a4121138"><ix:continuation id="F_000309_dcnt_490c96fc-196e-4fa9-8e3c-ab9b1e47aea8">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The primary financial statement impact upon adoption was the recognition, on a discounted basis, of the Company's minimum commitments under non-cancelable operating leases as right of use assets and obligations on the consolidated balance sheets. The adoption of ASC 842 resulted in the recognition of lease-related assets and liabilities of <span>$<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000332" name="us-gaap:OperatingLeaseRightOfUseAsset" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapAdjustmentsForNewAccountingPronouncementsAxis_us-gaapAccountingStandardsUpdate201602Member_20190331" decimals="-5" scale="6"><ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000333" name="us-gaap:OperatingLeaseLiability" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapAdjustmentsForNewAccountingPronouncementsAxis_us-gaapAccountingStandardsUpdate201602Member_20190331" decimals="-5" scale="6">13.7</ix:nonFraction></ix:nonFraction></span> million. The standard did not have a material impact on the Company's results of operations or cash flows.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Recently Issued Accounting Pronouncements Pending Adoption: <span style="font-style:normal;">In January 2017, the FASB issued ASU No.&#160;2017-04, </span>Intangibles-Goodwill and Other (Topic 350): Simplifying the Test for Goodwill Impairment<span style="font-style:normal;">. The standard simplifies the accounting for goodwill impairments and allows a goodwill impairment charge to be based on the amount of a reporting unit&#8217;s carrying value in excess of its fair value. This eliminates the requirement to calculate the implied fair value of goodwill or what is known as &#8220;Step 2&#8221; under the current guidance. This guidance is effective for annual and interim periods of public entities beginning after December&#160;15, 2019, with early adoption permitted. The Company</span><span style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;color:#000000;font-style:normal;"> is currently assessing the potential impact this ASU will have on its consolidated financial statements.</span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In June 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-13, <span style="font-style:italic;">Financial Instruments&#8212;Credit Losses</span> (Topic 326): Measurement of Credit Losses on Financial Instruments. This guidance requires the measurement of all expected credit losses for financial assets held at the reporting date based on historical experience, current conditions and reasonable and supportable forecasts. This guidance also requires enhanced disclosures regarding significant estimates and judgments used in estimating credit losses. The new guidance is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2019. Early adoption is permitted for fiscal years, and interim periods within those fiscal years, beginning after December 15, 2018. The Company is currently evaluating the impact that the adoption of this guidance will have on its consolidated financial statements.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">There were no other accounting standards recently issued that are expected to have a material impact on the Company&#8217;s financial position or results of operations.</p></ix:continuation></ix:continuation><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000295" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationDisclosureTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true" continuedAt="F_000295_dcnt_b9ee6269-6ff7-4288-9302-308d4dbb5202">
<div style="align:left;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.25%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2.</span></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Business Combination</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Exchange was completed on June&#160;1, 2018 and was accounted for as a reverse acquisition under the acquisition method of accounting as provided by the FASB Accounting Standards Codification 805, Business Combinations. Champion Holdings was deemed to be the acquirer for accounting and financial reporting purposes. The assets acquired and liabilities assumed as a result of the Exchange were recorded at their respective fair values and added to the carrying value of Champion Holdings&#8217; existing assets and liabilities. The Company incurred acquisition-related costs of approximately $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000335" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationAcquisitionRelatedCosts" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkycoLLCMember_us-gaapIncomeStatementLocationAxis_us-gaapOtherExpenseMember_20180401_20181229" decimals="-5" scale="6">6.9</ix:nonFraction> million for the nine months ended December 29, 2018, which were classified as other expense in the condensed consolidated statements of operations. <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000336" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationAcquisitionRelatedCosts" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkycoLLCMember_us-gaapIncomeStatementLocationAxis_us-gaapOtherExpenseMember_20180930_20181229" decimals="-6" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen" scale="6">No</ix:nonFraction> acquisition-related costs were incurred during the three months ended December 29, 2018. Additionally, the Company incurred approximately $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000338" name="us-gaap:AllocatedShareBasedCompensationExpense" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkycoLLCMember_us-gaapIncomeStatementLocationAxis_us-gaapSellingGeneralAndAdministrativeExpensesMember_20180401_20180630" decimals="-5" scale="6">6.0</ix:nonFraction> million in equity-based compensation expense related to former Skyline employees during the first quarter of fiscal 2019, which is recorded in selling, general, and administrative expenses in the condensed consolidated statements of operations. These types of costs were <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000334" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationAcquisitionRelatedCosts" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkycoLLCMember_us-gaapIncomeStatementLocationAxis_us-gaapOtherExpenseMember_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen" scale="6"><ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000337" name="us-gaap:AllocatedShareBasedCompensationExpense" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkycoLLCMember_us-gaapIncomeStatementLocationAxis_us-gaapSellingGeneralAndAdministrativeExpensesMember_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen" scale="6">no</ix:nonFraction></ix:nonFraction>t incurred during fiscal 2020.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The purchase price of the acquisition was determined with reference to the value of equity (common stock) of the Company based on the closing price on June&#160;1, 2018 of $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD_xbrlishares" id="F_000339" name="sky:CommonStockClosingPrice" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180601" decimals="2">33.39</ix:nonFraction> per share. The purchase price has been allocated to the assets acquired and liabilities assumed using their estimated fair values at June&#160;1, 2018, the closing of the Exchange. The purchase price and the allocation have been used to prepare the accompanying condensed consolidated financial statements. </p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000310" name="us-gaap:ScheduleOfRecognizedIdentifiedAssetsAcquiredAndLiabilitiesAssumedTableTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The purchase price was allocated as follows:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p>

<td valign="bottom" style="background-color:#CFF0FC;padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:15.48%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #000000; border-bottom:double 2.5pt #000000;white-space:nowrap;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000350" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationRecognizedIdentifiableAssetsAcquiredAndLiabilitiesAssumedNet" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapBusinessAcquisitionAxis_skySkylineMember_20180601" decimals="-3" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" scale="3">285,052</ix:nonFraction></p></td>
<td valign="bottom" style="background-color:#CFF0FC;padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;width:1%; border-bottom:double 2.5pt transparent;white-space:nowrap;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p></td>

</table></div></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Goodwill is primarily attributable to expected synergies from the combination of the companies, including, but not limited to, expected cost synergies through procurement activities and operational improvements through sharing of best practices. Goodwill, which is not deductible for income tax purposes, was allocated to the U.S. Factory-built Housing reporting unit.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Cash, trade receivables, other assets, accounts payable, and accrued liabilities were generally stated at historical carrying values given the short-term nature of these assets and liabilities. Intangible assets consist primarily of amounts recognized for the fair value of customer relationships and trade names and were based on an independent appraisal. Customer-based assets include the Company&#8217;s established relationships with its customers and the ability of those customers to generate future economic profits for the Company. The Company estimates that these intangible assets have a weighted average useful life of <ix:nonNumeric id="F_000351" name="us-gaap:AcquiredFiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsWeightedAverageUsefulLife" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" format="ixt-sec:durwordsen">ten years</ix:nonNumeric>.<span style="font-size:12pt;"> </span>Fair value estimates of property, plant, and equipment were based on independent appraisals and broker opinions of value, giving consideration to the highest and best use of the assets. Key assumptions used in the </p></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always" />

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The pro forma results are based on adding the historical results of operations of Champion Holdings and Skyline and adjusting those historical amounts for the amortization of intangibles created in the Exchange&#59; the increase in depreciation as a result of the step-up in fair value of property, plant, and equipment&#59; removing transaction costs directly associated with the Exchange&#59; removing equity-based compensation expense directly resulting from the Exchange&#59; reflecting the financing arrangements entered into in connection with the Exchange, and adjusting those items for income taxes. The pro forma disclosures do not give effect to the potential impact of current financial conditions, any anticipated synergies, operating efficiencies or cost savings that may result from the Exchange or any integration costs. The pro forma data is intended for informational purposes and is not indicative of the future results of operations.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Exchange Agreement provided that Champion Holdings was permitted to pay a capital distribution prior to completion of the Exchange to the extent it had cash in excess of debt and other debt-like items and unpaid Exchange fees and expenses. <p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Goodwill and Intangible Assets</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Goodwill</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Goodwill represents the excess of the cost of an acquired business over the fair value of the identifiable tangible and intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed in a business combination. At December 28, 2019 and March 30, 2019, the Company had goodwill of $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000405" name="us-gaap:Goodwill" contextRef="C_0000090896_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">173.5</ix:nonFraction>&#160;million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000406" name="us-gaap:Goodwill" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190330" decimals="-5" scale="6">173.4</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively. The change from March 30, 2019 was a result of the finalization of the allocation of net assets recognized in connection with the Exchange.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Intangible Assets</p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000314" name="us-gaap:ScheduleOfAcquiredFiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsByMajorClassTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company recognized finite-lived intangibles for customer relationships of $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000425" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedCustomerRelationshipsGross" contextRef="C_0000090896_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">43.1</ix:nonFraction> million and trade names of $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000426" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedTradeNamesGross" contextRef="C_0000090896_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">9.0</ix:nonFraction> million as a result of the allocation of the purchase price from the Exchange. The fair value of the customer relationship intangible asset was estimated using the multi-period excess earnings method of the income approach. The fair value of the customer relationship intangible asset was determined based on estimates and assumptions of projected cash flows attributable to the acquired customer relationships, the annual attrition rate of existing customer relationships, the contributory asset charges attributable to the assets that support the customer relationships, such as net working capital, property, plant, and equipment, trade name, and workforce, the economic life and the discount rate as determined at the time of the final valuation. The fair value of the trade name intangible asset was estimated using the relief-from-royalty method of the income approach. The fair value of the trade names intangible asset was determined based on estimates and assumptions used for the expected life of the intangible asset, the royalty rate and the discount rate that reflects the level of risk associated with the future cash flows as determined at the time of the final valuation. During the three months ended December 28, 2019 and December 29, 2018, amortization of intangible assets was $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000427" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190929_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">1.4</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000429" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180930_20181229" decimals="-5" scale="6">1.6</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively.&#160;&#160;During the nine months ended December 28, 2019 and December 29, 2018, amortization of intangible assets was $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000428" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">4.1</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000430" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180401_20181229" decimals="-5" scale="6">3.3</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively.</p>

The Credit Agreement provides for a revolving credit facility of up to $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000478" name="us-gaap:LineOfCreditFacilityMaximumBorrowingCapacity" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_us-gaapRevolvingCreditFacilityMember_us-gaapDebtInstrumentAxis_skyCreditAgreementMember_20180605" decimals="INF" scale="6">100.0</ix:nonFraction> million, including a letter of credit sub-facility of not less than $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000479" name="us-gaap:LineOfCreditFacilityMaximumBorrowingCapacity" contextRef="C_0000090896_srtRangeAxis_srtMinimumMember_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_us-gaapRevolvingCreditFacilityMember_us-gaapDebtInstrumentAxis_skyCreditAgreementMember_us-gaapShortTermDebtTypeAxis_us-gaapLetterOfCreditMember_20180605" decimals="INF" scale="6">45.0</ix:nonFraction> million. The revolving credit facility allows the Company to draw down, repay and re-draw loans on the available funds during the term of the Credit Agreement. During the three and nine months ended December 28, 2019, the Company repaid $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000481" name="us-gaap:RepaymentsOfLongTermDebt" contextRef="C_0000090896_deiLegalEntityAxis_skyChampionEnterprisesHoldingsLLCMember_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_us-gaapRevolvingCreditFacilityMember_us-gaapDebtInstrumentAxis_skyCreditAgreementMember_20190929_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">5.0</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000482" name="us-gaap:RepaymentsOfLongTermDebt" contextRef="C_0000090896_deiLegalEntityAxis_skyChampionEnterprisesHoldingsLLCMember_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_us-gaapRevolvingCreditFacilityMember_us-gaapDebtInstrumentAxis_skyCreditAgreementMember_20190331_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">15.0</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively, of amounts previously drawn on the revolving credit facility.</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Obligations under industrial revenue bonds are supported by letters of credit and bear interest based on a municipal bond index rate. The weighted-average interest rate at December 28, 2019, including related costs and fees, was <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000494" name="us-gaap:DebtWeightedAverageInterestRate" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyIndustrialRevenueBondsMember_20191228" decimals="4" scale="-2">3.78</ix:nonFraction>%. At March 30, 2019, the weighted average interest rate was <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000495" name="us-gaap:DebtWeightedAverageInterestRate" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyIndustrialRevenueBondsMember_20190330" decimals="4" scale="-2">3.62</ix:nonFraction>%. The industrial revenue bonds require lump-sum payments of principal upon maturity in <ix:nonNumeric id="F_000496" name="sky:IndustrialRevenueBondsMaturity" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyIndustrialRevenueBondsMember_20190331_20191228">2029</ix:nonNumeric>.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Credit Agreement contains covenants that restrict the amount of additional debt, liens and certain payments, including equity buybacks, investments, dispositions, mergers and consolidations, among other restrictions as defined. The Company was in compliance with all covenants of the Credit Agreement as of December 28, 2019.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Floor Plan Payable</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company&#8217;s retail operations utilize floor plan financing to fund the purchase of manufactured homes for display or resale. At December 28, 2019 and March 30, 2019, the Company had outstanding borrowings on floor plan financing agreements of $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000497" name="us-gaap:LineOfCredit" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyFloorPlanFinancingArrangementsMember_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">32.4</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000498" name="us-gaap:LineOfCredit" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyFloorPlanFinancingArrangementsMember_20190330" decimals="-5" scale="6">33.3</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively. Total credit line capacity provided under the agreements was $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000499" name="us-gaap:LineOfCreditFacilityCurrentBorrowingCapacity" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyFloorPlanFinancingArrangementsMember_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">48.0</ix:nonFraction> million as of December 28, 2019. <ix:nonNumeric id="F_000500" name="us-gaap:LineOfCreditFacilityDescription" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapCreditFacilityAxis_skyFloorPlanFinancingArrangementsMember_20190331_20191228">Borrowings are secured by the homes and are required to be repaid when the Company sells the home to a customer.</ix:nonNumeric>  </p></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">10</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company has operating leases for land, manufacturing and office facilities, and equipment. The Company's lease terms may include options to extend or terminate the lease when it is reasonably certain that the Company will exercise such option. The Company's leases do not contain material residual value guarantees or material restrictive covenants. <p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The discount rate used to measure a lease obligation should be the rate implicit in the lease&#59; however, the Company&#8217;s operating leases generally do not provide an implicit rate. Accordingly, the Company uses its incremental borrowing rate at lease commencement to determine the present value of lease payments. The incremental borrowing rate is an entity-specific rate which represents the rate of interest a lessee would pay to borrow on a collateralized basis over a similar term with similar payments.</p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000323" name="sky:ScheduleOfSupplementalCashFlowInformationRelatedToOperatingLeasesTableTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true">

<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.25%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</span></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Income Taxes<span style="font-weight:normal;"> </span></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For the three months ended December 28, 2019 and December 29, 2018, the Company recorded $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000569" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxExpenseBenefit" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190929_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">6.3</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000570" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxExpenseBenefit" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180930_20181229" decimals="-5" scale="6">4.4</ix:nonFraction> million of income tax expense and had an effective tax rate of <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000573" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190929_20191228" decimals="3" scale="-2">27.0</ix:nonFraction>% and <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000574" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180930_20181229" decimals="3" scale="-2">29.7</ix:nonFraction>%, respectively. For the nine months ended December 28, 2019 and December 29, 2018, the Company recorded $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000571" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxExpenseBenefit" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">20.5</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000572" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxExpenseBenefit" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180401_20181229" decimals="-5" scale="6">13.7</ix:nonFraction> million of income tax expense and had an effective tax rate of <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000575" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="3" scale="-2">28.2</ix:nonFraction>% and (<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000576" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180401_20181229" decimals="3" sign="-" scale="-2">25.5</ix:nonFraction>%), respectively. The change in the effective tax rate for the three and nine months ended December 28, 2019, compared with the same respective periods of the prior year, was primarily due to costs related to the Exchange including non-deductible equity-based compensation for which no tax benefit could be recognized.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company&#8217;s effective tax rate for the three and nine months ended December 28, 2019 differs from the federal statutory income tax rate of <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000577" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateReconciliationAtFederalStatutoryIncomeTaxRate" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190929_20191228" decimals="INF" scale="-2"><ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_xbrlipure" id="F_000578" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateReconciliationAtFederalStatutoryIncomeTaxRate" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF" scale="-2">21.0</ix:nonFraction></ix:nonFraction>% due primarily to the effect of non-deductible expenses, state and local income taxes and results in foreign jurisdictions. The Company&#8217;s effective tax rate for the three and nine months ended December 29, 2018 differed from the federal statutory rate primarily due to the effect of non-deductible expenses, state and local income taxes, one-time charges related to the Exchange and results in foreign jurisdictions and non-taxable entities.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During the nine months ended December 28, 2019, the Company&#8217;s uncertain tax position did not change. During the nine months ended December 29, 2018, the Company&#8217;s uncertain tax position decreased by $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000579" name="us-gaap:UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsPeriodIncreaseDecrease" contextRef="C_0000090896_20180401_20181229" decimals="-5" sign="-" scale="6">0.7</ix:nonFraction> million due to expiration of certain statutes of limitations. The Company estimates a $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000580" name="us-gaap:UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsReductionsResultingFromLapseOfApplicableStatuteOfLimitations" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="-5" scale="6">0.6</ix:nonFraction> million decrease to uncertain tax benefits in the next twelve months due to the expiration of statutes of limitations. The Company records interest and penalties related to uncertain tax positions as a component of income tax expense. Net interest and penalties for the periods presented herein were not significant.</p></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:4.25%;text-indent:-4.25%;font-size:9pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;">&#160;</p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000305" name="us-gaap:EarningsPerShareTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true">
<div style="align:left;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.25%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</span></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Earnings Per Share</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Basic net income (loss) per share (&#8220;EPS&#8221;) attributable to the Company was computed by dividing net income (loss) attributable to the Company by the average number of common shares outstanding during the period. Certain of the Company&#8217;s time-vesting restricted share awards are considered participating securities. Diluted earnings per common share is computed based on the more dilutive of (i) the two-class method, assuming the participating securities are not exercised or converted&#59; or (ii) the summation of average common shares outstanding and additional common shares that would have been outstanding if the dilutive potential common shares had been issued. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During the three and nine months ended December 28, 2019 and the three months ended December 29, 2018, the two-class method was more dilutive. The two-class method was not applicable to the computation for the nine months ended December 29, 2018 given the net loss recorded for that period. The number of shares used to calculate earnings per share prior to the Exchange was determined based on the exchange ratio, as defined in the Exchange Agreement.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</p><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000324" name="us-gaap:ScheduleOfEarningsPerShareBasicAndDilutedTableTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Prior to the Exchange, the Company was party to a Management Advisory Services Agreement (&#8220;Services Agreement&#8221;) with Centerbridge Advisors, LLC&#59; MAK Management L.P.&#59; and Sankaty Advisors, LLC (collectively, the &#8220;Managers&#8221;), affiliates of which collectively owned a majority of the units of Champion Holdings and the Company&#8217;s common stock (the &#8220;Principal Shareholders&#8221;), whereby the Principal Shareholders provided management, consulting, financial and other advisory services to Champion Holdings.&#160;Management fee expense during fiscal 2019, recognized prior to the Exchange, was $<ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_iso4217USD" id="F_000610" name="us-gaap:ProfessionalFees" contextRef="C_0000090896_us-gaapRelatedPartyTransactionAxis_skyServicesAgreementMember_us-gaapRelatedPartyTransactionsByRelatedPartyAxis_skyManagementAdvisoryMember_20180401_20190330" decimals="-5" scale="6">0.3</ix:nonFraction> million. The Services Agreement was terminated in connection with the Exchange. The </p></ix:nonNumeric>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">13</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always" />
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Skyline Champion Corporation</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Notes to Condensed Consolidated Financial Statements - Continued</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&#160;</p><ix:continuation id="F_000306_dcnt_ec5177c4-b6de-4e44-ae52-4a14df7bc875">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Management fee expense</span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">is included in selling, general</span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">,</span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and administrative expenses in the accompanying condensed consolidated statements of </span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">operation</span><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</span></p></ix:continuation><ix:nonNumeric id="F_000307" name="us-gaap:SegmentReportingDisclosureTextBlock" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" escape="true" continuedAt="F_000307_dcnt_1cb3c975-393d-4e21-9420-2b5139b3989c">

<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.25%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">4</span><span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</span></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-weight:normal;"></span>Segment Information</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Financial results for the Company's reportable segments have been prepared using a management approach, which is consistent with the basis and manner in which financial information is evaluated by the Company's chief operating decision maker in allocating resources and in assessing performance. The Company&#8217;s chief operating decision maker, the Chief Executive Officer, evaluates the performance of the Company&#8217;s segment primarily based on net sales, earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (&#8220;EBITDA&#8221;) and operating assets. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company operates in <ix:nonFraction unitRef="U_skySegment" id="F_000611" name="us-gaap:NumberOfReportableSegments" contextRef="C_0000090896_20190331_20191228" decimals="INF" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen">two</ix:nonFraction> reportable segments: (i) U.S. Factory-built Housing, which includes manufacturing and retail housing operations and (ii) Canadian Factory-built Housing. Corporate/Other includes the Company&#8217;s transportation operations, corporate costs directly incurred for all segments and intersegment eliminations. Segments are generally determined by geography. Segment data includes intersegment revenues and corporate office costs that are directly and exclusively incurred for each segment. Total assets for Corporate/Other primarily include cash and certain deferred tax items not specifically allocated to another segment.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.25%;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</p></ix:nonNumeric>
